\section doxygen Doxygen Quick Reference
Doxygen must be installed and accessible from the command line in order to document source code. The following files control doxygen behavior:

File|Description
----|-----------
common.doxyfile | DO NOT EDIT. Contains settings common to all projects.
project.doxyfile | Contains project-specific settings. Edit this file to change project title, versioning, etc.

\subsection doxy-req Requirements
-# Doxygen 1.8.11+
-# Graphviz 2.38+ (for fancy class diagrams)

\subsection doxy-linux Ubuntu/Xubuntu
The above packages can be installed with the following command:

    sudo apt-get install doxygen graphviz

\subsection doxy-win Windows
-# http://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen/download.html - for the latest Doxygen
-# http://www.graphviz.org/download/ - for the latest graphviz
-# May need to add these directories to PATH

\subsection doxy-run Running Doxygen
From an open console, cd to this project's doxygen directory, and run the following command:

    doxygen project.doxyfile

Doxygen will output HTML documentation to doxygen/html.

